Privacy Policy – Cheers
​
Last Updated: 17.05.2025
​
Welcome to Cheers! Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how Fiesta Studio AS ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal data when you use the Cheers mobile application ("App").
​
By using the App, you agree to the collection and use of your data as described in this Privacy Policy.
​
1. Information We Collect
When you use Cheers, we may collect the following types of information:
A. Information You Provide Directly
Account Information: If you create an account, we may collect your email, username, and password.
Profile Information: If applicable, you may provide profile details such as your gender, preferences, or other optional details.
User Content: Any content (e.g., messages, posts, images) you voluntarily share within the App.
B. Information We Collect Automatically
Device Information: Model, operating system, app version, and unique device identifiers.
Usage Data: How you interact with the App, including feature usage and time spent.
IP Address & Location Data: If enabled, we may collect your approximate location.
C. Information from Third Parties
Payment Processors: If you make a purchase, payment details are processed securely via [App Store / Google Play]. We do not store your payment details.
Analytics Providers: We may use third-party analytics (e.g., Google Analytics, Firebase) to understand user behavior.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
✅ Provide and improve the App’s functionality.
✅ Personalize your experience and offer relevant content.
✅ Process payments and manage subscriptions.
✅ Ensure security, prevent fraud, and enforce policies.
✅ Comply with legal obligations.
3. How We Share Your Information
We do not sell your personal data. However, we may share data in the following cases:
With Service Providers: To help us operate the App (e.g., cloud storage, analytics, customer support).
For Legal Compliance: If required by law, such as responding to legal requests or protecting our rights.
With Your Consent: If you explicitly agree to share your data with third parties.
4. Your Rights and Choices
Depending on your location, you may have rights under privacy laws like GDPR (EU) or CCPA (California):
🔹 Access & Update: You can review and edit your account information.
🔹 Delete Data: Request account deletion and removal of your data.
🔹 Opt-Out of Tracking: Disable analytics tracking via app settings.
🔹 Withdraw Consent: Stop data collection by discontinuing use of the App.
To exercise your rights, please contact us at
support@fiestastudio.cc
.
5. Data Security
We implement security measures to protect your data, including:
🔒 Encryption of sensitive data.
🔒 Secure servers and controlled access.
🔒 Regular security audits to prevent unauthorized access.
However, no system is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
6. Data Retention
We retain your data only as long as necessary for the purposes outlined in this policy. If you delete your account, we will erase your data unless legal obligations require retention.
7. Children’s Privacy
Sex Adventure is intended for users 18 years and older. We do not knowingly collect data from children under 18. If we discover such data, we will delete it immediately.
8. International Data Transfers
If you are located outside EU, your data may be processed in the United States, where privacy laws may differ. By using the App, you consent to such transfers.
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. If changes are significant, we will notify you via in-app notice or email. Continued use of the App after changes means you accept the updated policy.
10. Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
📧
support@fiestastudio.cc
🌍 fiestastudio.cc
​
By using Cheers, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agreed to this Privacy Policy.